<div id="banner">
	<h1>final(?) segway update</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Well, it&#8217;s almost time to return the Segway and we&#8217;ve all but lost interest in it. Working on the movie kept us going for a little while longer but since I posted it the Segway has pretty much stayed in its place in the corner, off. I think we&#8217;ve explored everything there is to do with it, and now it&#8217;s just uninteresting.</p>

<p>It&#8217;s not like we have much of a practical use for it, especially not now. It&#8217;s so cold and snowy outside that every time we go out we have to suit up in so much clothing that we&#8217;d be protected from a nuclear blast. And it&#8217;s not like we have anyplace to go: everything&#8217;s closed for Xmas and school&#8217;s out.</p>

<p>On a related note, <a href="http://www.theregister.co.uk/content/54/28682.html">San Francisco has banned the Segway</a>. Sigh, the one city where it might actually be useful.</p>

<p class="posted">posted December 29, 2002 09:54 AM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_personal">Personal</a>)  <a href="000777" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

